			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h2>Our Basis for Giving Determines our Emotions</h2>
<p>&nbsp;<br />
<a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/tithe-offering-giving.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1638" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 15px;" title="tithe offering giving" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/tithe-offering-giving.jpg" alt="" width="267" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>When the government forces us to pay taxes, it&#8217;s a form of giving that&#8217;s <strong>involuntary</strong>.</p>
<p>When you file your annual income tax report and calculate how much you owe, it&#8217;s a form of <strong>involuntary</strong> giving.</p>
<p>Because it&#8217;s forced upon us, the emotion associated with involuntary giving is bitterness and resentment. Now consider what happens when we want to give.</p>
<p>The pleasure received watching a loved one open a gift from us and screech with delight is hard to beat. Watching their face break into a huge smile is worth every penny you paid for the gift.</p>
<p>Think back to the last time you went out to a restaurant with others and picked up the tab. It made you feel good. You held your head a little higher when you left. Why?</p>
<p>Because you wanted to give your money away! It was completely <strong>voluntary</strong>.</p>
<p>When we&#8217;re forced to give, we do it grudgingly.</p>
<p>When we freely give, we do it with a <strong>cheerful heart.</strong></p>
<h2>Enjoy this podcast episode as I share a message I gave on our emotions surrounding giving.</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>When we’re FORCED to give, we do it grudgingly. When we FREELY give, we do it with a cheerful heart. New episode &#8211; <a href="http://t.co/gVCOTGUY" title="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/33">stewardshipweekly.com/33</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Glen Steinson (@StewardshipWeek) <a href="https://twitter.com/StewardshipWeek/status/209462521952870401" data-datetime="2012-06-04T01:52:11+00:00">June 4, 2012</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><br />
