			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>This past weekend, my wife and I attended a &#8216;<strong>Weekend to Remember</strong>&#8216; marriage getaway hosted by FamilyLife Today.</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1347" style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 15px;" title="FamilyLife Today Weekend to Remember" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/FamilyLife-Today-Weekend-to-Remember.jpg" alt="" width="301" height="118" />It was an <strong>incredible experience</strong> that we highly recommend to anyone who thinks their marriage could be strengthened by some quality time together (away from the kids) at a Christian conference.</p>
<p>Each week in this podcast, I talk about being good stewards of what the Lord has entrusted to our care; our income &amp; assets, our time &amp; our talents. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">I&#8217;m embarrassed to admit it</span>, but over the course of the initial 26 episodes, I completely overlooked the greatest gift that God has put into my care &#8211; <strong>my wife</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>The itinerary included</strong>; group lessons with the keynote speakers, &#8216;making it personal&#8217; time to individually complete assignments in our workbooks, sharing sessions where we sat one-on-one with our spouse to discuss certain topics, and a date night (complete with lots of open communication &amp; romance).</p>
<p>The weekend also included a few sessions where the men were in one conference room and the women were in another. Since God has created us uniquely different, sometimes we need to be reminded that we have different styles of <strong>communication</strong>, different levels of <strong>emotion</strong> and different requirements when it comes to <strong>sexual intimacy</strong>. Everything was discussed. No subject was off limits. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Honestly</span> &#8211; it was really great to see so many subjects covered over the three days.</p>
<p>Listen to the podcast as I share my thoughts on how things went and tell you about our Saturday night date!</p>
<p>After you&#8217;ve listened, be sure to visit FamilyLife Today.</p>
<p>For the Canadian site, click <a href="http://powertochange.com/familylife/events/weekend-to-remember/" target="_blank">HERE</a>. For the American site, click <a href="http://www.familylife.com/site/c.dnJHKLNnFoG/b.5846045/k.8C0A/Weekend_to_Remember__Marriage_Getaway.htm?fromhp=WTRbox" target="_blank">HERE</a>.<br />
