Each week in this podcast, I talk about being good stewards of what the Lord has entrusted to our care; our income &amp; assets, our time &amp; our talents. I'm embarrassed to admit it, but over the course of the initial 26 episodes, I completely overlooked the greatest gift that God has put into my care - my wife.

The itinerary included; group lessons with the keynote speakers, 'making it personal' time to individually complete assignments in our workbooks, sharing sessions where we sat one-on-one with our spouse to discuss certain topics, and a date night (complete with lots of open communication &amp; romance).

The weekend also included a few sessions where the men were in one conference room and the women were in another. Since God has created us uniquely different, sometimes we need to be reminded that we have different styles of communication, different levels of emotion and different requirements when it comes to sexual intimacy. Everything was discussed. No subject was off limits. Honestly - it was really great to see so many subjects covered over the three days.

