			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div id="attachment_1223" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 275px">
	<img class=" wp-image-1223 " style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 00px; margin-right: 20px;" title="Julia Denning" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Julia-Denning.jpg" alt="" width="275" height="421" />
	<p class="wp-caption-text">1 of 10 grandchildren</p>
</div>
<p>You know how I always mention that Stewardship Weekly is a show where you can share your stories with the listeners? This is one of those episodes! Today I have a listener who wanted to share her life story on the podcast &#8211; so we made the arrangements, I called her on the phone and we recorded the conversation!</p>
<p>As you listen to this episode, you&#8217;ll quickly realize that <strong>this dear sister in the Lord is sincere about how she uses her time</strong>. For her entire married life, she has remained focused on using her time wisely to strengthen her marriage, teach her children and edify her grandchildren.</p>
<p>Through talking with her, I learned that there were many times in her life when it would have been a lot easier to follow the ways of the world rather than the path of righteousness that was laid out in front of her. Every step in tandem with Jesus Christ her Saviour, along the often challenging road of life, confirmed that she had made a wise decision when she surrendered her life to Him in faith.</p>
<p>Listen as Julia Denning speaks in her own words.<br />
