			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h3>2011 was my <strong>Year of Change</strong>. Like it or not, life was altered dramatically.</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_1109" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 146px">
	<img class=" wp-image-1109  " style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;" title="Countdown Club" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Logo-Colour-w-words-209x300.jpg" alt="" width="146" height="210" />
	<p class="wp-caption-text">(I walked away)</p>
</div>
<p>Instead of being a children&#8217;s club commander, a volunteer worker for a gospel sign distributor, landlord of two rental properties and the brilliant mind behind a christian housing website (that didn&#8217;t exactly work out), the end of the calendar year has me <strong>removed from all four of these roles</strong>. My own well laid plans have been thwarted by someone who has a clearer picture of my future than I do &#8211; someone who has my best interests in mind and loves me enough to die on a cross for my sins.</p>
<p>Before getting into the main content for the episode, I open with a few more thoughts on <strong>Twitter</strong>. As previously mentioned, I&#8217;m now using the little blue birdie to expand the reach of the show and will use it productively to promote each episode, make announcements about upcoming guests and &#8211; <strong>most importantly</strong> &#8211; to interact with you! Please find and follow the podcast; <span style="color: #000080;"><strong>@StewardshipWeek</strong></span>. Tweet. Tweet.</p>
<p>I then share a voice message that <a title="Episode 12 – Don’t Disinherit The Lord In Your Will" href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/dont-disinherit-the-lord-in-your-will/" target="_blank">Scott Thomson</a> left on the listener feedback line about last weeks interview with <a title="Episode 22 – Rob Kuban reveals the Secret of Generosity" href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/rob-kuban-reveals-the-secret-of-generosity" target="_blank">Rob Kuban</a>. Be sure to bookmark Scott&#8217;s site &#8211; <a href="http://digitalsojourner.com" target="_blank">Digital Sojourner</a> - Thoughts on the Christian life as we sojourn together through the modern world. The team of writers over there are extremely active at their keyboards and post content on an almost daily basis. Very sound, biblical teaching.</p>
<div id="attachment_1104" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 270px">
	<img class=" wp-image-1104 " title="christian housing" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/christianhousD16aR03aP01ZL-300x146.jpg" alt="" width="270" height="131" />
	<p class="wp-caption-text">(I pulled the plug)</p>
</div>
<p><strong>The majority of this episode is some story-telling on my part</strong>. You get to hear what the Lord has been doing to alter my course this past year and set me in a completely different direction. I am no longer involved in a couple of local ministries that I was supporting. We have sold two townhouses that we were generating rental income from. A website that had been my focus for quite a number of years now has been shut down. Why all this you ask? I&#8217;ll tell you (in the podcast).</p>
<p>On a closing note, the winner of the draw for the book &#8220;<strong>the Secret of Generosity</strong>&#8221; is <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/jws-financial-coaching-podcast/id403380338" target="_blank">Jon White</a>. Congratulations!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
