			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h2>3 Common Mistakes and How to Overcome Them</h2>
<h3>Practical Advice from a Christian Financial Coach</h3>
<p>Ben Davies is a financial services broker who faithfully serves his clients with sound advice based on the time-proven money principals found written in the Bible. Through his association with various different companies, he&#8217;s able to offer both investment and insurance solutions for businesses and individuals alike. <strong>Above and beyond all the products that he can offer his clients is a personal touch that really makes him stand out from others in the over-crowded industry</strong>. Using one-on-one coaching sessions, Ben cuts through all the numbers and paperwork to get down to the real issues &#8211; the attitude of the heart and how those feelings influence long term plans.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1021" title="Ben &amp; Glen" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Ben-Glen-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">In our discussion, Ben shares how he&#8217;s utilized Crown Financial Ministries material within his business, at his church and in his own training and development. By following God&#8217;s plan for financial stewardship, Ben teaches friends and family how to identify goals, develop plans, set incremental targets and stay committed for the long haul. <strong>We also discuss the importance of accountability partners</strong> and diligence.</p>
<p>While coaching clients, both at his office and in their homes, he&#8217;s heard what&#8217;s worked well for them and what their biggest challenges have been. Over the years, <strong>he&#8217;s identified the 3 most common mistakes people make</strong> with their money and offers his wisdom on how to overcome them. Enjoy listening to this extended interview.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
