			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-17" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 20px;" title="SW 150x150" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GlenSteinsonD05bR01aP01ZL_150x150pixels.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" />It&#8217;s great to speak with fellow believers who have a like-minded passion for biblical finance! In this episode, I had the great pleasure of interviewing a new friend of mine who also hosts a weekly podcast.</p>
<p><strong>Steve Stewart</strong> is a self proclaimed &#8216;Personal Finance Architect&#8217;.  He&#8217;s the voice behind the microphone over at the <strong><a href="http://www.moneyplansos.com/" target="_blank">Money Plan SOS</a></strong> podcast and his desire is <strong>not</strong> to help people manage their debt.  His desire is to teach people how to <strong>eliminate</strong> debt. As he coaches clients, both in-person and through his show, he guides them on how to use a budget to build a firm foundation and then how to secure the four financial walls around them, topped off with a good roof for fiscal shelter.  His &#8216;<strong>Financial House of Freedom</strong>&#8216; serves as an excellent example of how to move from the bondage of credit to the freedom of wealth.</p>
<p>One of his favorite passages of scripture to teach from is <strong>Matthew chapter 25</strong>.  The parable of the talents is deeply practical for believers as we need to understand how God wants us to manage what we have for His glory and good pleasure.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-829" title="Steve Stewart" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Steve-Stewart.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="250" /></p>
<p>While at his website, be sure to watch some of Steve&#8217;s video&#8217;s.  Here&#8217;s the one that was referenced in the show &#8211; <a href="http://www.moneyplansos.com/credit-cards-are-like-cereal" target="_blank">Credit Cards Are Like Cereal</a>.</p>
<p>Steve is also a regular guest over at the <a href="http://financialexcellence.net/about-us/" target="_blank">Living In Financial Excellence</a> podcast that is hosted by Matt Wegner.</p>
