			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-17" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 20px;" title="SW 150x150" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GlenSteinsonD05bR01aP01ZL_150x150pixels.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></p>
<h2>Laundry Room Renovations</h2>
<p>As the tagline in the header reads, Stewardship Weekly is also about honoring the Lord with our time. My thoughts for this episode are drawn from a personal story.  Over the past few days I&#8217;ve been covering the laundry room walls with chipboard and building some shelves where the kids can pick up their clean clothes.  I was initially planning on recording some extra podcast episodes and working on the <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/spreadsheet-spending-plan-video-tutorial-in-the-making/" target="_blank">Spreadsheet Spending Plan</a> video tutorials, but God had other plans.  He wanted to shift my focus away from the income and assets and teach me what it really means to be a good steward of my time.  Listen as I share how passages of scripture from both Psalm 32 and Acts 9 influenced my attitude.</p>
<h2>The Whatley&#8217;s Reach Out To Their Community</h2>
<p>I love hearing someone speak another language.  In this episode, I&#8217;m joined by Alan &amp; Rachel Whatley who are home in Canada for a few months visiting friends and family before heading back to Indonesia where they are serving the Lord with <a href="http://usa.ntm.org/" target="_blank">New Tribes Mission</a>.</p>
<p>Joined by their two young children, the Whatley&#8217;s are faithfully following Christ&#8217;s example and reaching out to those who are lost in their sins.  Their weekly routine often involves in-home bible studies, children&#8217;s ministry, office support for other team members and an endless list of repair &amp; maintenance projects at the missions station.  I honestly believe that every newsletter and e-mail we&#8217;ve received from Alan &amp; Rachel has had at least one picture of Alan with a hammer in his hand!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-814" title="Indonesian Girl" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Indonesian-Girl.jpg" alt="" width="425" height="282" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Listen as they share their story of God&#8217;s leading them both into missionary work as a result of attending a conference together in their early marriage.  Their adventure into learning of God&#8217;s faithfulness to provide for them is heard as they recount how they gradually increased their giving in increments of 10%.  Once they finished their training and moved overseas, the Lord continued to reveal His hand of provision over and over again.</p>
<p>Be sure to visit the web site at <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com">Stewardship Weekly</a>
