			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h2><span style="color: #ff0000;">A special welcome to readers of Jen&#8217;s ebook &#8220;Living Beyond Awesome&#8221;!</span></h2>
<p>Since starting this podcast back in June of 2011, I&#8217;ve had lots of fun making new friends online through various blogs, forums and email. When I first heard Bob &amp; Jen interviewed on another podcast, I felt compelled to contact them. <strong>Right from the initial response I received back from Jen, I knew this episode would be something special!</strong></p>
<p>Once you&#8217;ve listened to their story (either using the podcast options above or subscribing through <strong><a href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/stewardship-weekly/id442079137" target="_blank">iTunes</a></strong>) please call my voice mail feedback line and leave a message of encouragement for them! Jen always has positive and uplifting words for others and so, playing your recorded message back to her is a way that we can return the favour.</p>
<p>We know you&#8217;ll enjoy this episode &#8211; <strong>listen &amp; enjoy!</strong></p>
<h2></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Bob &amp; Jen McDonough Interview</h2>
<p>The other night I had the great privilege of speaking with the McDonough family of Minnesota. Theirs is a remarkable journey of a Christian couple who have faced incredible challenges head-on and are a <strong>true testimony of the Lord&#8217;s faithfulness to those who choose to serve Him</strong> with their income and assets.</p>
<p>Back in 2009, two life changing obstacles stood looming in front of them; a <strong>burden of debt</strong> that was crushing them slowly, and the devastating news that their son had an <strong>incurable medical condition</strong>. Today you&#8217;ll hear their story. Armed with the wisdom found in the book of Proverbs and a financial coach that they now consider to be a close friend, Jen and Bob, along with their 4 children embarked on a life-long journey with the hope that someday they&#8217;ll hear their Savior say &#8220;<strong>well done good and faithful servants</strong>&#8220;.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-766" style="margin-top: 50px; margin-bottom: 50px;" title="Bob &amp; Jen McDonough" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Bob-Jen-McDonough-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" /></p>
<p>After we hear from Mom and Dad, their daughter Maggie gives us a firsthand report of how the entire family is following the pattern; work, give, save, then spend. A lot of people do it the way the credit card companies and retail stores want us to, which is to spend first then work forever to try to pay it down. And once that pattern starts, often there isn&#8217;t any money left over to save or give.</p>
<p>A brief interview with their son Robbie wraps up the episode.  This is a brave young man who, through his medical issues, motivated his parents to be responsible <strong>Money Managers for the Lord</strong>. If Robbie was completely healthy and the trips back and forth to the medical center in Denver weren&#8217;t needed, just think &#8211; where would his family be today? Probably where they were back at the start of 2009 &#8211; buried in debt and living their lives thinking everything was normal and that life was fine.</p>
<p><strong>Check out Jen&#8217;s websites &#8211; <a href="http://www.fieldofdebt.com/ourstory.php" target="_blank">Field of Debt</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.livingbeyondawesome.com" target="_blank">Living Beyond Awesome</a></strong><br />
Podcasts referenced in this episode &#8211; <a href="http://www.moneyplansos.com/" target="_blank">Money Plan SOS</a> &amp; <a href="http://financialexcellence.net/" target="_blank">Living In Financial Excellence</a></p>
<address> </address>
<p>Be sure to visit the web site at <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com">Stewardship Weekly</a>
&nbsp;
Subscribe and listen to every new episode via <a href="itpc://feeds.feedburner.com/stewardshipweekly">iTunes</a> (one click subscription)
&nbsp;</p>
