We know you'll enjoy this episode - listen &amp; enjoy!

 
Bob &amp; Jen McDonough Interview
The other night I had the great privilege of speaking with the McDonough family of Minnesota. Theirs is a remarkable journey of a Christian couple who have faced incredible challenges head-on and are a true testimony of the Lord's faithfulness to those who choose to serve Him with their income and assets.

Back in 2009, two life changing obstacles stood looming in front of them; a burden of debt that was crushing them slowly, and the devastating news that their son had an incurable medical condition. Today you'll hear their story. Armed with the wisdom found in the book of Proverbs and a financial coach that they now consider to be a close friend, Jen and Bob, along with their 4 children embarked on a life-long journey with the hope that someday they'll hear their Savior say "well done good and faithful servants".

After we hear from Mom and Dad, their daughter Maggie gives us a firsthand report of how the entire family is following the pattern; work, give, save, then spend. A lot of people do it the way the credit card companies and retail stores want us to, which is to spend first then work forever to try to pay it down. And once that pattern starts, often there isn't any money left over to save or give.

A brief interview with their son Robbie wraps up the episode.  This is a brave young man who, through his medical issues, motivated his parents to be responsible Money Managers for the Lord. If Robbie was completely healthy and the trips back and forth to the medical center in Denver weren't needed, just think - where would his family be today? Probably where they were back at the start of 2009 - buried in debt and living their lives thinking everything was normal and that life was fine.

Check out Jen's websites - Field of Debt &amp; Living Beyond Awesome
Podcasts referenced in this episode - Money Plan SOS &amp; Living In Financial Excellence

