			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h2>Tithes &amp; Offerings, Pure Gold &amp; a Pure Heart</h2>
<p>In this episode of Stewardship Weekly, I begin by telling you a little bit about our Labor Day weekend at Camp Li-Lo-Li.  I have to admit that <strong>I underestimated the responsibilities of a Camp Director</strong> as I had been hoping to meet with John Benson while we were there.  Although we did enjoy a short time around the fire with him one evening, I was not able to sit down and record an interview for the podcast.  As always, all the families at camp had a fantastic time and <strong>the Lord was honored</strong> through the singing, ministry and fellowship enjoyed by everyone.</p>
<p>This week, I share that I have spent some time in 1<sup>st</sup> Kings chapters 6 &amp; 7 reading the passages about the temple construction. It’s mind-boggling to think how much gold was used in the building project.  Absolutely everything was overlaid with pure gold, the cost of which was almost too great to measure.  What’s amazing to consider is that <strong>a lot of this gold came a from the free will offerings of the Israelites</strong>.  We read in 1<sup>st</sup> Chronicles 29:9 that “the people rejoiced for they had offered willingly to the Lord.”</p>
<p>As one who uses a <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/spreadsheet-spending-plan-video-tutorial-in-the-making/" target="_blank">spreadsheet spending plan</a> to manage our finances, and having just signed the <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Financial-Covenant-with-God.pdf" target="_blank">Financial Covenant With God</a>, I’ve been thinking about the condition of my heart when giving.  Am I always giving to the Lord willingly and with a joyful heart, or am I in part following a routine of dispersing funds as dictated by our budget?</p>
<p>A familiar passage in 2<sup>nd</sup> Corinthians 9:7 reads  “so let each one give as he purposes in his heart, not grudgingly or of necessity, for <strong>God loves a cheerful giver</strong>”.</p>
<p>The 2<sup>nd</sup> half of the podcast is a couple of short messages from <strong>Larry Ball</strong>.   As he shares his thoughts, Larry draws some <strong>comparison between having our portion in this world versus having our portion and fulfillment in Christ.</strong></p>
<p>The episode concludes with a playback of the messages you hear when you call into the <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Voice-Mail-Image.jpg" target="_blank">Listener Feedback Line</a>.   You can hear the 3 different options and get familiar with the voicemail.  Please call.  I’d love to hear from you!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
