To get us started this week, Ismail makes a startling statement. “If sin was never introduced, we would never have had the need for money because we would still have been in perfect harmony with God and with one another and therefore had no need to buy and sell.”

One of the bitter consequences of sin is selfishness. Men and women live for themselves trying to quench the thirst in their souls. The book of Ecclesiastes, in chapter 2, reminds us that these pursuits are all in vain. One can only derive true fulfillment through the Lord Jesus Christ. We came into this world with nothing and will likewise leave with the same.

