			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><h3>Podcast Outline;</h3>
<h2>Book Review &#8211; Money, Possessions &amp; Eternity by Randy Alcorn</h2>
<p>As mentioned back in episode 2, I have read quite a number of excellent books on biblical finance and have selected a handful that I&#8217;d like to encourage you to look into.  For this first review, I purposely selected my favorite book.</p>
<p>This is a heavy duty read with 422 pages.  But don&#8217;t let that turn you off.  Money, Possessions &amp; Eternity is <strong>not</strong> milk &#8211; <span style="text-decoration: underline;">it&#8217;s all meat</span>.  Not the chewy kind though.  <strong>This is the delicious meat that falls off the bone and melts in your mouth</strong>.</p>
<p>The author, Randy Alcorn shares his thoughts in a logical and well thought out structure and gives chapter and verse reference to support each of his findings.  The verses are <strong>not</strong> taken out of context to fit his beliefs &#8211; they are carefully studied on their own and then conclusions drawn from the truth that they contain.  A lot of other &#8216;Christian&#8217; books on finance draw their own beliefs and then go hunting to find verses to support those beliefs.  Not this book.</p>
<p>Check out Randy&#8217;s blog &#8211; <a href="http://www.epm.org/blog" target="_blank">here</a></p>
<p>Listen to part of the book &#8211; <a href="http://www.christianaudio.com/money-possessions-and-eternity-randy-alcorn" target="_blank">here</a></p>
<p>A blank copy for you to pray about and sign &#8211; <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Financial-Covenant-with-God.pdf" target="_blank">Financial Covenant with God</a></p>
<h2>Transfer Treasurers On Ahead Home</h2>
<p>I&#8217;ve recently observed a handful of Mexican workers living north of the border for the summer.  Their simple but sufficient living quarters provided a great illustration for where we should store our treasure.</p>
<p>Their 3 bedroom trailer located on the edge of the vegetable fields where they diligently work each day, isn&#8217;t filled with extravagant luxuries.  Instead of buying all the latest and greatest that money can buy here, they make their way to the bank each week and transfer their money &#8211; on ahead home to Mexico.</p>
<p>Enjoy the podcast as we use this example to focus our thoughts and hearts &#8211; on ahead home to heaven.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Be sure to visit the web site at <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com">Stewardship Weekly</a>
&nbsp;
Subscribe and listen to every new episode via <a href="itpc://feeds.feedburner.com/stewardshipweekly">iTunes</a> (one click subscription)
&nbsp;</p>
