This week however, the plans have changed.  The entire episode is an interview I just had with a friend of mine named Peter Zein.  My original intent was to edit the recording and bring it down to 20 mins or so, but, one of the reasons I'm hosting the Stewardship Weekly podcast is to have the show be an encouragement to the listening audience.  After going over the content numerous times, I decided that it would be in your best interest to hear almost the entire conversation.  Once you hear it, I'm sure you'll agree.
About Our Guest
Peter Zein is a man who will never achieve financial independence.  It's not because he makes foolish money decisions.  It's not because he lacks the knowledge required for long term planning.  Quite the opposite.  He'll never achieve financial independence - because he doesn't want to.  If financial independence is reaching the point in your life where you feel safe and secure with what you have and no longer have to trust in anyone else - he doesn't want it.

