			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></p>
<p>This episode opens with a brief story of a family going on a much anticipated trip to Florida.  One of the young siblings loses his little wallet containing his spending money!  Find out what happened.</p>
<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;"><strong>Jesus the Wise Coach</strong></span></p>
<p>We then spend some time together looking at <strong>Matthew 6:19-21</strong> and thinking about <strong>how</strong> and <strong>where</strong> we store up our treasure.</p>
<p>A good coach figures out what motivates someone and then uses that knowledge to drive them to achieve excellence!  That is exactly what we see the Lord doing in this passage.  God knows that we, as emotional beings, are motivated by rewards.  And the reward in this case is treasure!  (He made us and gave us those emotions).  Now He wants to use those emotions for our own good.</p>
<p>First he gives us a warning about our treasures &#8211; don’t keep them where you will lose them.  He then presents the preferred alternative &#8211; a guaranteed safe place where they will <span style="text-decoration: underline;">yield dividends for eternity!</span>  He didn&#8217;t give us a warning and then end the conversation and walk away &#8211; He told us what we should do to ensure that we don’t lose it.</p>
<p>Christ Jesus wants us to have the true rewards (the treasure) once we reach our final destination &#8211; not focus on the temporal ones here on earth!</p>
<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold;"><strong>Lessons with Larry</strong></span></p>
<p>I first welcomed Larry Ball onto the show in episode 1.  A few weeks ago, he sat down at my desk in front of the microphone and recorded a series of short, ‘on-the-fly’ messages for Stewardship Weekly.  Don’t be mistaken, these are golden nuggets of rich truths.  Some people might take days to put together what he shares here on the show.</p>
<p>In this episode, Larry shares two different thoughts that tie in nicely with our study of where you store your treasure.  The first discussion is on the world’s obsession with collecting ‘stuff’.  Materialism is the focus and distraction of the society we are living in. In the second, he looks at the vineyard parable and the misguided emphasis of seizing the inheritance &#8211; the here and now.</p>
<p>Be sure to visit the web site at <a href="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com">Stewardship Weekly</a>
