			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Waiting is hard.  Waiting when we <strong>know</strong> when something is going to happen is hard.</p>
<p>Waiting when we <em><strong>don&#8217;t</strong></em> <strong>know</strong> when something will happen is even harder!</p>
<p>In this episode, I start the show by reflecting on the life of King David to learn about patience, self-control and how to wait on the Lord&#8217;s timing.  This past week, there have been a number of things that have driven me to <strong>think about what really matters</strong> &#8211; making things happen based on my schedule, or being obedient to what He has called me to do and waiting for things to happen in His perfect time.</p>
<p>In the middle of the show, there is a <strong>great story from a young couple</strong> who saw the Lord&#8217;s timing play out in the middle of their real estate shopping when purchasing their first home.  It&#8217;s a back and forth account of making multiple visits to multiple properties &#8211; all the while trying to decipher God&#8217;s plan for their new family.</p>
<p>The episode wraps up with my personal story of trying to find a <strong>scuba diving</strong> partner, <strong><em>almost</em> purchasing a motorcycle</strong> and having a heart-felt discussion with <strong>my life coach</strong> (my Mom).  I share some details on our line-of-credit and our 10 year old son teaching me the proper way to making a &#8220;major&#8221; purchase.</p>
<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;">Show Contents -</span></p>
<ul>
<li>David wants to build the Lord a house.  God says, <strong>no</strong>, you will <strong>not</strong> build it.</li>
<li>&#8221; Thanks for the offer but <em>your</em> timing is not <em>my</em> timing. I have plans to have another person build it.&#8221;</li>
<li>David had the resources to go ahead and build it anyways &#8211; but he didn&#8217;t.</li>
<li>Was building a house for the Lord a bad thing? Not in and of itself, but the timing was wrong.</li>
<li>&#8220;Unless the Lord builds the house, they labour in vain&#8221; (another subject but applicable for this reference).</li>
<li>Key verses read 2 Samuel 7:1-13 then 25</li>
<li>Story submitted by <strong>Hanniel &amp; Jannilea Ghezzi</strong></li>
<li><strong></strong>1 Samuel 2:30 &#8211; &#8220;Those who honor Me, I will honor&#8221;</li>
<li>What about our testimony to those who are watching what we do?  Thoughts about family, friends and ministry.</li>
</ul>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-454" title="Ghezzi blue background" src="http://www.stewardshipweekly.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Ghezzi-blue-background-300x192.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="192" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #333399;">Have you ever had to wait on the Lord&#8217;s timing for something in your life? </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #333399;">Call the toll-free listener feedback line and leave a voice mail with your brief story.</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #333399;">What was it you were waiting for?  How long did you have to wait?  How did the Lord respond?</span></strong></p>
