		<itunes:summary>Waiting is hard.  Waiting when we know when something is going to happen is hard.

Waiting when we don't know when something will happen is even harder!

In this episode, I start the show by reflecting on the life of King David to learn about patience, self-control and how to wait on the Lord's timing.  This past week, there have been a number of things that have driven me to think about what really matters - making things happen based on my schedule, or being obedient to what He has called me to do and waiting for things to happen in His perfect time.

In the middle of the show, there is a great story from a young couple who saw the Lord's timing play out in the middle of their real estate shopping when purchasing their first home.  It's a back and forth account of making multiple visits to multiple properties - all the while trying to decipher God's plan for their new family.

The episode wraps up with my personal story of trying to find a scuba diving partner, almost purchasing a motorcycle and having a heart-felt discussion with my life coach (my Mom).  I share some details on our line-of-credit and our 10 year old son teaching me the proper way to making a "major" purchase.

Show Contents -

	David wants to build the Lord a house.  God says, no, you will not build it.
	" Thanks for the offer but your timing is not my timing. I have plans to have another person build it."
	David had the resources to go ahead and build it anyways - but he didn't.
	Was building a house for the Lord a bad thing? Not in and of itself, but the timing was wrong.
